==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Retentive
<hw>Re*ten"tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧tentif</ets>.]</ety> <def>Having power to retain; <as>as,
a <ex>retentive</ex> memory</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor airless dungeon, nor strong links of iron,⟦br⟧
Can be <qex>retentive</qex> to the strength of spirit.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retentive</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Retentive
<hw>Re*ten"tive</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which retains or confines;
a restraint.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retentively</ent>⟦br⟧
